                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 30.186,
                                "byte_start": 74014,
                                "byte_stop": 194804,
                                "text": "-- is next in number 70-73, Miller against California."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 30.186,
                                "stop": 31.754,
                                "byte_start": 194804,
                                "byte_stop": 201074,
                                "text": "Mr. Marks, you may proceed."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 31.754,
                        "stop": 332.613,
                        "byte_start": 201074,
                        "byte_stop": 1404483,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 17862,
                            "name": "Burton Marks",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/burton_marks",
                            "last_name": "Marks",
                            "roles": null,
                            "thumbnail": null,
                            "length_of_service": 0,
                            "identifier": "burton_marks"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 31.754,
                                "stop": 35.094,
                                "byte_start": 201074,
                                "byte_stop": 214448,
                                "text": "Mr. Chief Justice, may it please the Court."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 35.094,
                                "stop": 50.514,
                                "byte_start": 214448,
                                "byte_stop": 276097,
                                "text": "Purpose of my argument to which eventually I hope will tie-in with the questions which are raised on the certiorari, I am going to make some statements which may sound as if they are pejorative or demeaning, they are not so intended."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 50.514,
                                "stop": 59.49,
                                "byte_start": 276097,
                                "byte_stop": 312042,
                                "text": "I express them merely as a statement of what I have experienced in the defense of obscenity cases."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 59.49,
                                "stop": 86.082,
                                "byte_start": 312042,
                                "byte_stop": 418412,
                                "text": "My first observation is that, as far as I can tell, probably, no member of this Court has gauged either the prosecution or the defense of an obscenity case where you are required to deal with the various rules of law and procedure which have set forth \u2013 set by this Court concerning the handling of such a case."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 86.082,
                                "stop": 99.702,
                                "byte_start": 418412,
                                "byte_stop": 472852,
                                "text": "Therefore, it\u0027s somewhat equivalent as my wife used to say, \u201cYou can understand that I have a lot of pain when I have a child, but you will never experience it.\u201d"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 99.702,
                                "stop": 106.889,
                                "byte_start": 472852,
                                "byte_stop": 501586,
                                "text": "There is a lot of pain in the trial in trying to work out the rules which have been established by this Court."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 106.889,
                                "stop": 128.93,
                                "byte_start": 501586,
                                "byte_stop": 589776,
                                "text": "The second proposition is that this Court has expressed or perhaps not expressed, but vocalized the assumption that lower courts and lower judges, both State and Federal, will obey the mandates of this Court when it comes to deciding on obscenity case."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 128.93,
                                "stop": 154.198,
                                "byte_start": 589776,
                                "byte_stop": 690817,
                                "text": "This case is an illustration of the fact that such an assumption is totally false and is an illustration of what, in my opinion, is a immutable proposition that when you are dealing with obscenity or dealing with pornography that for the most part it is a visceral turn off to the majority of the courts and which you in front off."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 154.198,
                                "stop": 163.862,
                                "byte_start": 690817,
                                "byte_stop": 729478,
                                "text": "And thus you may, as in this case present un-controvertible proof, uncontested proof that the material is protected."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 163.862,
                                "stop": 194.679,
                                "byte_start": 729478,
                                "byte_stop": 852776,
                                "text": "Un-controverted proof and irrevocable proof that there has been a prior judicial decision as it was in this case, uncontested by the state that the material was constitutionally protected and that nevertheless the defendant must endure what in this case case was a seven-week trial plus some other various procedural propositions which I will outline."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 194.679,
                                "stop": 258.721,
                                "byte_start": 852776,
                                "byte_stop": 1108985,
                                "text": "And I think this might also illustrate, why this Court, I think, was absolutely wrong in Harris v. Younger or Younger v. Harris and its progeny in holding that one criminal prosecution is not any type of a hardship upon a defendant at least in the area of obscenity because the criminal and it might also illustrate the fact, something that I am going to urge to this Court, that there should be an attempt to delineate the difference between an obscenity prosecution and a prosecution under the ordinary rules of criminal procedure because they do not jibe and for the past 10 or 15 years since Roth courts have been trying to tear or take the obscenity issues and weave them and fold them into the area or environment of a criminal trial."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 258.721,
                                "stop": 264.656,
                                "byte_start": 1108985,
                                "byte_stop": 1132705,
                                "text": "And the rules of criminal procedure just do not meet the issues."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 264.656,
                                "stop": 288.213,
                                "byte_start": 1132705,
                                "byte_stop": 1226954,
                                "text": "A suggestion is going to be then if my analysis is correct that this Court must faction some procedural rules for the conduct of obscenity cases along the lines of Mapp versus Ohio because as this Court well know there has been a total chaos in this area."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 288.213,
                                "stop": 305.62,
                                "byte_start": 1226954,
                                "byte_stop": 1296545,
                                "text": "Now, the first proposition that I have with respect to the rules laid down by this court is that there is a new irreconcilable conflict between the decisions of this Court."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 305.62,
                                "stop": 319.03,
                                "byte_start": 1296545,
                                "byte_stop": 1350148,
                                "text": "Irreconcilable in the sense that they are logically inconsistent, however, one court pointed up and I have not been able to find the case, that logic is the dominion and not the master of the law."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 319.03,
                                "stop": 332.613,
                                "byte_start": 1350148,
                                "byte_stop": 1404483,
                                "text": "So, we can avoid that little proposition that perhaps this Court has been logically inconsistent because it really doesn\u0027t matter if we can fashion some rules where we can handle what we are doing."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 332.613,
                        "stop": 334.832,
                        "byte_start": 1404483,
                        "byte_stop": 1413364,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15107,
                            "name": "William O. Douglas",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/william_o_douglas",
                            "last_name": "Douglas",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2751,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": -969127200,
                                    "date_end": 185004000,
                                    "appointing_president": "Franklin D. Roosevelt",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2751"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32781,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 56651,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/william_o_douglas.png"
